<br>
Basic math:<br>
Frosty: 12 / 22 (.54 higher is better)<br>
Hammer: 9 / 20 ( . 45 )<br>
Tae Ew War Maul: 33 / 36 ( .9 )<br>
 <br>
<br>
With FBSS:<br>
Frosty: 12 / 18 ( .6 )<br>
Hammer: 9 / 17 ( .52 )<br>
Maul : 33 / 30 (1.1)<br>
<br>
With FBSS and Celerity:<br>
Frosty: 12 / 13 (.92)<br>
Hammer: 9 / 14 ( .64 )<br>
Maul: 33 / 21 ( 1.57 )<br>
<br>
The BAH is still pretty nice:<br>
FBSS and Celerity: 40 (44) / 28 (1.43 / 1.57)<br>
<br>
When you are dealing with percentages, take the same percent chunk off a larger number gives you better results.<br>
<br>
Of course my personal goal:<br>
Stone bladed axe of Dismay with FBSS and SLTW: 44 / 24 (1.8)<br>
Dismay with COF and SLTW: 44 / 22 ( 2)<br>
Dismay with 40% belt and Shissar: 44 / 21 ( 2.1)<br>
<br>
(<br>
What the heck, while I'm dreaming:<br>
Feartouched Greatsword with FBSS and Shissar: 46 / 21 (2.1)<br>
Twisted Steel Bastard Sword: 53 / 24 (2.21)<br>
And the sexiest sword in the whole game in my mind:<br>
Bloodied Berserker's Blade<br>
With FBSS and Shissar: 52 / 21 ( 2.4 )<br>
With COF and Shissar: 52 / 20 ( 2.6 )<br>
)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Because haste is a percentage, people really really need to learn to take that into consideration for weapon's decisions.  You just DON'T get the same return with the same haste.  Especially when you are talking about 2hs where the damage bonus scales with delay.<br>
<br>
Anyone know what the damage bonus is on the maul compared to the BAH?  Does the maul have stats?  The BAH has no stats and a 45 point lifetap, also 4 of it's damage is resistable.  That means it can either have the same ratio as the maul or slightly worse, but will have a slightly (maybe 2 or 3 points?) larger damage bonus.<br>
<br>
The maul is better, I would say, but the BAH is a great choice depending on how much the maul runs.  Either way, it should kick do well against both of those one handers, depending on your haste gear.  I'd say your best upgrade would be to either A) sell your weapons, buy a BAH and upgrade haste if you only have an FBSS B) Sell your weapons and get Dismay for significant step up in DPS. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uwyrdlan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wyrdlan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0> at: 10/9/02 7:10:25 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umistwolfeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MistwolfEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 123<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/9/02 7:26:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4093.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tae Ew war maul vs. 2 1handers</span><hr size=1> 1) Get a Tae Ew War maul or Savage stone axe (same ratio) for a cheap 2hs thats nice ratio (and fast)<br>
